y stories about the lives of individuals but critical reflections on subjects who are directly involved in, and affected by, politics in Canada. This book makes for lively reading that stimulates fresh thinking about political biography and the direction of political history more generally.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aPoliticianszCanadaxBiographyxHistory and criticism. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh1 aAzzi, Stephen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBonder, Jennifer Levin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBothwell, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBryden, P.E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDonaghy, Greg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDonaghy, Greg, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHillmer, Norman, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLackenbauer, P. Whitney, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLackenbauer, P. Whitney, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMcKercher, Asa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMilloy, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPerras, Galen Roger, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSauer, Angelika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTouhey, Ryan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311127214608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2022z978311127419508iTitle is part of eBook package:dD